definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl) and (5E,8E,11E,14E)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.
An optically active form of O-isobutyrylcarnitine having (R)-configuration.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl substituent both at positions 1 and 2 is specified as (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.
An optically active form of O-2-methylbutyrylcarnitine having (R)-configuration.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as acetoacetyl.
